raw_data.title: Program Manager
raw_data.description: Is responsible for leading, organizing, directing and coordinating one or more projects for the client. Is responsible for assigning tasks, recruiting resources, working within deadlines and timeframes, reviewing and supervising the work of personnel. Acts as a communication liaison between various personnel involved in projects including the user, client, project managers and other Government points of contact.

raw_data.title: Software Developer
raw_data.description: Responsibilities include a team leadership role in the design, development, modification, and integration of application software, utilizing frameworks (i.e. JAVA, dot.net, etc.), and has experience on database programming. Has essential technical knowledge in conducting unit testing of software programs, developing user interface screens, and transaction processing steps. Works under the supervision of senior level software developers and staff. Is involved in the training of junior level software developers and project team members to successfully complete task orders, objectives, and keep the project moving on track. Communicates with project managers, software analysts, and senior level executives to complete projects in a timely manner.

raw_data.title: Network & Systems Administrator
raw_data.description: Has leadership experience and is responsible for a leadership role in the installing networks, configuration management, and disaster recovery configurations. Has a strong technical knowledge in wide-area networks, network segments, intranet and extranet development, and network optimization. Is involved in the training of junior level administrators and project team members to successfully complete task orders, objectives, and keep the project moving on track. Communicates with project managers, software analysts, and senior level executives to complete projects in a timely manner.

raw_data.title: Infrastructure Engineer
raw_data.description: Responsibilities include taking on a team leadership role in the installation, configuration, modification and integration of network software, vendor software, internally-developed software, database server configuration, creation of database systems, and providing access to application servers. Has a strong technical background and knowledge in operating systems used in the project (i.e. Linux). Is involved in the training of junior level infrastructure engineers and project team members to successfully complete task orders, objectives, and keep the project moving on track. Communicates with project managers, software analysts, and senior level executives to complete projects in a timely manner.

raw_data.title: Business Analyst
raw_data.description: Responsibilities include a team leadership role gathering business requirements from the client (internal or externally facing), developing business process management (BPM) processes, designing and developing functional requirement documents, nonfunctional requirements, UAT Testing, pre-production validation, and user sign off. Has strong background knowledge and experience in business management processes. Is involved in the training of junior level business analysts and project team members to successfully complete task orders, objectives, and keep the project moving on track. Communicates with project managers, software analysts, and senior level executives to complete projects in a timely manner.

raw_data.title: Web Developer
raw_data.description: Responsibilities include taking on a team leadership role in the understanding, designing, utilizing, maintaining, modifying client server technologies (e.g. JAVA and .net). Has experience and technical knowledge in products (e.g. AngularJS, Java-Script, etc.), messaging of data, transaction processing, creation of wire frames, creation of web portals, and integration with back-end systems. Is involved in the training of junior level web developers and project team members to successfully complete task orders, objectives, and keep the project moving on track. Communicates with project managers, software analysts, and senior level executives to complete projects in a timely manner.

raw_data.title: Systems Support Analyst
raw_data.description: Responsibilities include taking on team leadership role in the support of various internally and externally developed software, troubleshooting, ticket and case management. Other important duties include root-cause analysis, system monitoring, database monitoring, batch monitoring, and escalation to 2nd and 3rd level of support. Works under the supervision of senior level support analysts and staff. Is involved in the training of junior level support analysts and project team members to successfully complete task orders, objectives, and keep the project moving on track. Communicates with project managers, software analysts, and senior level executives to complete projects in a timely manner.

raw_data.title: Project Manager
raw_data.description: Is responsible the main team leadership role and support in the planning, coordinating, direction and management task orders and objectives instructed by the Program Manager. Works closely under the supervision of the Program manager and senior level Project managers to successfully complete task orders. Is involved in communicating along side the Program Manager with the end users, customers, and Government points of contact (i.e. Contracting Officers). Other responsibilities includes making the main frame project plan, tracking of progress and setbacks, developing and modifying project objectives and technical feasibility. Performing risk assessments, report escalation, and relationship maintenance between involved parties and stakeholders.

raw_data.title: Product Manager
raw_data.description: Responsible for the developing product pricing, marketing of product launch, positioning strategies, providing strategic requirements, developing prototypes as well as translational liaison between involved parties in the government sector. Assists project personnel in creating, maintaining, and optimizing the scope of the product and activities of priority. Works closely with team members, executives, and engineering teams to deliver timely and functionally active resources.

raw_data.title: Architect
raw_data.description: Responsible for leading architecture team in the creation, design, maintenance of various large-scale and complex computer systems, network systems, and security systems in information technology. Utilizes computer design software to construct models, test efficacy of program code, and implementation of network models. Works to modify currently used systems to optimize performance of network software functionality. Communicates with the software development team to establish system specifications and requirements for database and network optimization. Coordinates and communicates with teams involved in the project including software developers, network engineers, and senior level project executives to successfully complete objectives and goals of the project.

raw_data.title: Database Engineer
raw_data.description: Responsibilities consist a team leadership role in designing data solutions, developing prototypes, architecture, program coding and module simulation to meet demands of the project. Management and completion of routine task orders, modifying database objectives and planning. Extracts data accurately and precisely and provides information to involved personnel. Other duties include manual testing of data for maintenance, upgrading and updating relevant data information as well as integration of new software and technologies. Effectively communicates with other team members, points of contacts, managers and higher executives to successfully complete goals and objectives of the project. Also trains and educates junior engineers and organization members.

raw_data.title: Database Administrator
raw_data.description: Responsibilities include a team leadership position in the planning, designing, maintaining databases, modifying existing database structure, generation of reports, controlling access to data by users, and monitoring activity pertaining to data access. Actively performs installation and configuration of database software including Oracle and Microsoft SQL server. Performs routine recovery and back-up of data for contingency purposes, maintains archived data, and report generation. Has a strong technical knowledge background in database theory and design. Plays in integral role in coordinating and communicating with users, government contract officers and executives to successfully keep database security and integrity in place.

raw_data.title: System Analyst
raw_data.description: Responsibilities consist of a team leadership role in examining current software systems installed, creating specifications of system requirements, making decisions on system selection, implementation of new planned system integration. Other duties pertain to monitoring of system efficacy, meeting the needs of system specifications, development of cost analysis, and project timeline production and projection. Works under the supervision of senior analysts and employees. Consults with business analysts, project managers, and higher points of contact to modify, create, and maintain effective system capabilities. Is responsible for training junior analysts and involved staff and has a strong technical background and knowledge base.

raw_data.title: Subject Matter Expert (SME)
raw_data.description: Responsibilities consist of a team leadership role in the design of system requirements, planning technical approach to systems, generation of design specifications for software development, and creation of computer algorithms. Provides oversight of the design, development, modification, integration, and implementation of system software. Is involved in the review of technical user manuals, user guides, as well in the communication between team members. Works in a team environment, acts as liaison and effectively communicates between workers to successfully give direction on the domain of expertise. Articulately and professionally communicates between project team members, executives, and software developers to keep the project goals on track and deliverables completed in a timely manner.  Effectively trains junior level subject matter experts and other team members to maximize on productivity.

raw_data.title: QA/QC Analyst
raw_data.description: Responsibilities include a team leadership role in unit testing, functional testing, integration testing, and user acceptance testing (UAT). Other duties include performance testing, resiliency testing of software programs, capturing and repairing defects in software, as well as developing regression scripts. Is involved in the training and education of the junior level QA/QC analysts and project team members. Communicates with government points of contacts, project managers, and project executives to successfully complete task orders and objectives.
